# User Grid App

This is a simple web application that fetches user data from an API and displays it in a grid layout. The app includes a navbar with a brand name and a "Get Users" button to trigger the API call. While fetching data, a loader is displayed to provide visual feedback.

## Features

- Responsive user grid layout
- Navbar with brand name and "Get Users" button
- Fetches user data from API: [https://reqres.in/api/users?page=1](https://reqres.in/api/users?page=1)
- Displays loader while fetching data

## Technologies Used

- HTML
- CSS
- JavaScript

## How to Use

1. Clone or download this repository.
2. Open `index.html` in a web browser.
3. Click the "Get Users" button to fetch and display user data.
4. Enjoy the responsive user grid layout!

## Folder Structure

- `index.html`: Main HTML file.
- `styles.css`: CSS file for styling.
- `script.js`: JavaScript file for fetching data and interaction.

## Credits

- Loader animation: [W3Schools](https://www.w3schools.com/howto/howto_css_loader.asp)
- API used: [ReqRes](https://reqres.in/)

